subentries 22,23 and a large number of new subentries
were created after optical character recognition
of PDF  pages 12-42, added doi.
Corrected for flux attenuation and multiple
scattering by the MAGGIE code except for double
differential cross sections.
By compiler (2016-09-22): Angular-integrated cross
sections in Appendix A of LA-3765 (1967) are slightly
different from those in Tables I+II of LA-3765 (1967)
and Tables 1+2 of Nucl.Phys.A107(1968)139. Values in
Appendix A are adopted in this EXFOR entry except for
NE102A plastic scintillator (12.7 in diam.,
2.5 cm thick)
5.8 cm in diam, 15.2 cm in length, energy
resolution of about 9.5% for the 0.67 gamma-ray
8 MV Van de Graaff
En=3.35 and 4.83 MeV
en=5.74 and 7.5 MeV
Flight path of 2.3 m
Nai detector details
Separated Li isotopes (purity>99%, 2 cm diam, 2.54 cm
long) canned in thin Al containers.
Cylindrical polythene (0.51 cm diam, 1.9cm long) for
cross section normalization.
Empty can runs were done for background subtraction.

The energy spectra are intended only to show the
continuum neutrons. The cross sections for the
discrete peaks given in the energy spectra have not
been corrected for multiple scattering and
attenuation. The cross sections for discrete peaks are
given separately and have been corrected properly.

Corrected for
a.Attenuation of the incoming neutron beam including
the effects of multiple scattering of the neutrons
and a l/r2 factor, where r is the distance between
the neutron source and the scattering sample,
differs for different parts of the scattering
sample.
b.Attenuation of outgoing gamma rays.
c.Gamma rays caused by Compton scattering within the
sample.
No information on source of uncertainty
